==English==

===Verb===
'''enjoin'''

# {{transitive}} To [[lay]] upon, as an [[order]] or [[command]]; to give an [[injunction]] to; to [[direct]] with [[authority]]; to [[order]]; to [[charge]].
# {{transitive}} {{law}} To [[prohibit]] or [[restrain]] by a [[judicial]] [[order]] or [[decree]]; to put an [[injunction]] on.

